00655       PROF_READ_GHOST_ELEMS_BEGIN_BEGIN
00656 
00657         // first need to create contiguous list of boundaries ...
00658         T* sendK = NULL;
00659 
00660       if(m_uipElemScatterMap.size()) {
00661         sendK = new T[dof*m_uipElemScatterMap.size()];

00664

00666         // add dof loop ...

00673       updateContext ctx;

00682             m_uipElemRecvProcs[i], m_uiCommTag, m_mpiCommActive, req );
00683         ctx.requests.push_back(req);

00685 
00686       //*********** Send ****************//

00691             m_uipElemSendProcs[i], m_uiCommTag, m_mpiCommActive, req );

00695       // Increment tag ....

00887       };

00951         } else {
00952           //nodal and non-ghosted
00953           for (unsigned int i = m_uiElementBegin; i < m_uiElementEnd; i++) {
00954             if ( ! (m_ucpOctLevels[i] & ot::TreeNode::NODE ) ) {
00955               continue;
00956             }
00957             for (unsigned int j = 0; j < dof; j++) {
00958               out[dof*i+j] = array[dof*vecCnt + j];
00959             }
00960             vecCnt++;
00961           }
00962           for (unsigned int i = m_uiElementEnd; i < m_uiPostGhostBegin; i++) {
00963             // add the remaining boundary nodes ...

00966               continue;
00967             }

01087   inline unsigned char DA::getChildNumber() {
01088 #ifdef __DEBUG_DA__
01089     assert(m_bIamActive);
01090 #endif
01091 
01092     if( m_bCompressLut && m_ucpLutMasksPtr[(m_uiCurrent << 1) + 1] ) {
01093       return ( m_ucpSortOrdersPtr[m_uiCurrent] );
01094     }else {
01095       unsigned int lev = m_ucpOctLevels[m_uiCurrent] & ot::TreeNode::MAX_LEVEL;
01096       unsigned int len = (unsigned int)(1u << ( m_uiMaxDepth - lev ) );
01097       unsigned int len_par = (unsigned int)(1u << ( m_uiMaxDepth  - lev +1 ) );
01098 
01099       unsigned int i = m_ptCurrentOffset.xint() % len_par;
01100       unsigned int j = m_ptCurrentOffset.yint() % len_par;
01101       unsigned int k = m_ptCurrentOffset.zint() % len_par;
01102 
01103       i /= len;
01104       j /= len;
01105       k /= len;
01106 
01107       return static_cast<unsigned char>((k << 2) + (j << 1) + i); //4*k+2*j+i
01108     }

03764   template <typename T>
03765     void injectNodalVector(ot::DA* dac, ot::DA* daf, unsigned int dof,
03766         std::vector<T>& fVec, std::vector<T>& cVec, void (*setZero)(T&)) {
03767 
03768       dac->createVector<T>(cVec, false, false, dof);
03769 
03770       T* cArr = NULL;
03771       T* fArr = NULL;
03772       dac->vecGetBuffer<T>(cVec, cArr, false, false, false, dof);
03773       daf->vecGetBuffer<T>(fVec, fArr, false, false, true, dof);
03774 
03775       for(int i = 0; i < (dof*(dac->getLocalBufferSize())); i++) {
03776         (*setZero)(cArr[i]);
03777       }
03778 
03779       daf->ReadFromGhostsBegin<T>(fArr, dof);
03780       daf->ReadFromGhostsEnd<T>(fArr);
03781 
03782       if(dac->iAmActive()) {
03783         for(dac->init<ot::DA_FLAGS::WRITABLE>(), daf->init<ot::DA_FLAGS::WRITABLE>();
03784             dac->curr() < dac->end<ot::DA_FLAGS::WRITABLE>();
03785             dac->next<ot::DA_FLAGS::WRITABLE>()) {
03786           unsigned int idxC = dac->curr();
